l Fackenheim -- t14. Irving Greenberg: A Jewish Dialectic of Hope -- t15. Feminist Jewish Philosophy: A Response -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aEncounters of Consequence provides an introduction to and deeper analysis of the situation of Jewish philosophy beginning in the last century. It charts Jewish philosophy's engagement with modernity and post-modernity along two overlapping axes-issues and persons-which often intersect. Key issues in modern Jewish philosophy are raised, including: the nature of Judaism and Jewish identity, the quests for meaning and continuity, the value of remaining a Jew, and the relevance of Jewish law, as well as the challenges of secularism, modern history (including the Holocaust), feminism and religious pluralism. Featured are many philosophers of encounter: Franz Rosenzweig, Martin Buber, and Emmanuel Levinas, as well as Joseph Soloveitchik, Gershom Scholem, Arthur Cohen, Eliezer Schweid, Emil Fackenheim, and Irving Greenberg.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 0aJewish philosophersxHistoryy20th century. 0aJewish philosophyxHistoryy20th century. 0aPhilosophy, Moderny20th century. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertASP eBook Package Backlist 2008-2015z978311068814640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781618110138423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781618110138.jpg  a978-3-11-068814-6  ASP eBook Package Backlist 2008-2015c2008d2015  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2H